inn1.comm: runs in and bowls one on a length but down the leg side for it to be called a wide
back of a length this time and around off stump, not much to be done with apart from playing it out to point
short of a good length again, this time Guptill taps it with soft hands in front of point who runs in quickly to pick up the ball but Baz is quicker in stealing the single
ripper from Shoaib, landed back of a length like the earlier deliveries did, but this one straightened after pitching, and Baz was beaten comprehensively as he prodded at it outside off
goes a bit fuller, and that much is enough for Baz, remains in the crease and with tremendous bat speed sends it racing through cover for the first boundary, got it right in the middle of the blade
a touch shorter in to the body, and defended towards mid on
this one comes back in from short of a length outside off, Baz decided to let it go, and it bounced just over the stumps, phew
does a Shoaib, starts off with a wide ball down the leg side
gets one full on the pads, and drives it elegantly wide of mid on for a single
continues to stray down the pads, and is flicked instantly backward of square leg for a couple
pretty close to be a wide, this time on the off side, he was looking to go across Baz, but it was just inside the marker, and he got away with it
goes a bit shorter now, outside off stump with the angle, he goes back and pushes it to point
gets the angle going across the right-hander just outside off, and Baz leaves it alone
brings bat in front of pad to turn this length ball to square leg
141 kph fullish delivery on the off stump, driven without power towards mid off
the bouncer arrives from Shoaib, and well directed too, forcing Guptill to go underneath it
118 kph slower ball, bang on target, excellent control from Shoaib, Guptill is a touch early on the forward defensive
thumped off the back foot, but Shafiq saves a certain boundary with a full-length dive at cover, it was timed really well, and was travelling fast
again Shoaib goes short of a good length, the ball comes on nicely to Guptill, who stands on the back foot and punches it to Shafiq at cover
just short of a length in the zone outside off stump, left alone this time
excellent length delivery, very close to off stump, Baz shows good judgment in letting it go
comes charging down the track looking to smash it through the covers, but Sohail sprays it very far wide outside off stump
gets it back in the corridor outside off with the angle, and Baz leaves it alone
he has absolutely murdered this one, it was a tad fuller in length, he was to the pitch of it in a flash, and swung it over mid off for a six, one leg in the air as he made contact
sprays it wide again, this time down the leg side

that will be the end of Baz, he was looking for that lofted shot over mid off again, Sohail was wise enough to bowl it a bit wider outside off this time, Baz went through with the shot anyway after haring down the track, and got an edge off the toe end of the bat that ended up safely in the hands of Kamran, McCullum has wasted his opportunity at the top of the order
goes down the leg side again, it looked to have come off the thigh pad, but umpire Davis thought hard and decided that was a wide
pushes a length ball to mid off and takes off for the single, and makes it in the end to get off the mark
angling away from the right-hander outside off, and left alone, finally Tanvir's over ends, but he has removed Baz
stays in the crease and punches a length delivery around off towards cover
gets one on the pads and misses out on the flick, but they are quick to steal a single as the ball rolls away into the on side
in the channel outside off on a length, Guptill shoulders arms
Shoaib has displayed such fine control in this spell, another length delivery on off stump is defended off the front foot
for the first time he serves up one shortish and wide outside off, Guptill decided to have a go at it, and gets it over point for a boundary, it was intentionally played in the air
goes very full and on middle this time, is driven straight to mid on
fullish delivery on off stump, Ryder gets the front forward and pushes it back towards the bowler
Jesse is away, Tanvir bowled it on the pads, and Ryder just flicked it in a flash to the left of square leg, it was in the air but beautifully timed
punched off the back foot to the man at short extra cover
gets forward and defends a length ball towards mid off
looks to force this one off the back foot through cover, but the ball was not short enough for the shot, and he mistimes it to point
Tanvir gets away with a fullish and wide delivery, it was there to be put away, but Ryder ended up forcing it straight to short extra cover
Guptill is getting nicely behind the line of the full deliveries from Shoaib, drives another one of them to mid on
straightens a bit from a length around off, but Guptill is right behind it with the forward defensive push
looks to loft a full delivery over mid on, but got it off the inner half of the bat as the blade turned in his hands, and the ball went high in the air, but safely cleared the infield over midwicket
tucks this back of a length delivery backward of square for a single
waits for a length delivery to arrive around off stump, and guides it with an open bat face to backward point
too straight from Shoaib, worked away in front of square on the leg side, there is no one at square leg, no one at midwicket, and by the time the ball is fielded, they take a comfortable couple
targets the area over mid on with the attempted loft, but gets an inside edge on to pad as he swings at the length delivery angled across him close to off stump
pushes hard at this one and gets it over a diving short extra cover on the bounce for a single wide of mid off
Ryder swings, and connects neatly, it was angled into him on the pads, and he helped it past short fine leg for a boundary
fuller, but again on the pads, Tanvir is wasting the new ball here, this time it is flicked in the air over midwicket
better from Tanvir, around off  on a length, Ryder stays in the crease and plays it out to point

dropped he almost gets a wicket with a full delivery on the pads, Ryder swung it in the direction of Razzaq at a very fine short fine leg, who dived to his left, and got one hand to the ball, before dropping it as he fell to the ground, very tough chance that
short and fast in to the body, fended fine down the leg side, Kamran tidies up
slower ball outside off this time, lovely variation from Shoaib, defended off the back foot

how did that get to the boundary? it was a nasty short one on the stumps, Guptill had already shaped up for the pull, but it climbed so quickly on to him that he decided to get out of the shot, too late, and he ended up swatting it in the air over cover, where it just trickled in to the boundary
goes hard at a length delivery outside off stump from the crease, and the thick edge flies to the left of third man for another four, frustration for Shoaib
gets a short one  in to the body, and works it towards square leg for a single
on the pads, flicked away backward of square leg for another single. he has played that shot well today
huge from Jesse! it was marginally short and sitting up around leg stump, Ryder lifted it with a clean swing over midwicket all the way in to the stands
goes for the pull again, this one is not short enough and he bottom edges it through square leg
he goes over wide long on this time, Ryder is connecting them cleanly here, it was wide outside off stump on a length, and he went across to hammer it down the ground for another maximum
the slower one arrives around off stump, he plays it out to point
103 kph slower ball, makes no difference to Jesse, it was fuller on the stumps, and he lifted it without any fuss whatsoever high over long on for the third six of the over, good catch in the stands
gets away with this one, it was short and he went for another big one, but top-edged the pull high over midwicket, but it drops exactly in between the two fielders converging on the ball
short of a length outside off stump, punched towards cover
he is playing them with utmost ease now, taps a short of a length delivery to backward point off the back foot
not a bad delivery at all, finishing around off stump, but Jesse opens the face of the bat at the last instant and runs it down to third man
Gul has not given away anything this over, another one just back of a length around off is defended by Guptill
still more short of a length stuff, this time in to the body, played out to midwicket off the back foot
steals a single to mid on, it was hit off the back foot too, but Tanvir took ages to get down, he took still more time to finally throw the ball, and by then Guptill was safely home
tossed up outside off stump, defended to cover
on middle this time, and worked in front of square leg off the front foot
tucks him with the angle, played back down the track
ooh, down the track comes Jesse, looking to go through extra cover, but ends up finding precisely that man inside the ring
this time he pings the gap between mid off and extra cover, it was tossed up fuller and he leaned in to the drive to get the placement perfectly
another maximum, his fourth, Hafeez continues to flight the ball, Ryder lifted it straight down the ground over mid off, he didn't need to move a lot, just stood there and lofted it with good timing
played out to point off the back foot
gets squared up, Guptill, it was dug in back of a length in to the batsman, who wanted to tuck it through midwicket, but got an edge down the track
mistimes the drive this time, it was fuller , and he launched in to the shot, but got an inside edge on to pad
gets the run now, goes back and punches this back of a length delivery wide of mid off to bring Ryder on strike
calmly glided down to third man for a single
gets on the front foot and defends a length delivery towards mid on
starts off with the wrong 'un from round the stumps, and beats Jesse who pushes at it from the crease
coming in with the angle, swung away through square leg
tossed up delivery just around off stump, guided to short third man
gets some drift and it comes in to Guptill who gets into a tangle as he gets on the back foot and looks to force it away
quicker now, he gets on the front foot and pushes out  towards extra cover
good over from Shahid, Guptill gets forward and defends one into the covers
141 kph and full on the stumps, he stays in the crease and clips it wide of mid on

mistimes the pull off the short delivery, but gets it into the gap past a slow Shoaib at mid on, and that will be 50 for Jesse, has connected almost everything so far, and is looking good for much more
crashed through cover, made some room outside leg, and just hammered a length delivery past the packed cordon in that region
Gul goes for the yorker, gets it just outside leg stump, Ryder digs it out to midwicket

my word, how good a shot is that, it was a nasty short one from Gul, and even as it got big on Ryder, he hooked it on one leg over the man at short fineleg, was off balance as he played the shot, but with that timing, he'll get another six
almost gets another one past short fine, Gul goes leg side again, and Ryder flicks deftly, but Shafiq with a diving stop prevents the boundary
Guptill continues to defend stoutly at the other end
alright he can hit them too, Afridi pitches it short and Guptill latches on, pulling it in a flash flat over midwicket, the sixes continue to flow
defended in to the off side
draws him forward with a tossed up one, played out towards cover
again he lures him forward and gets him to drive airily this time, but in the gap through covers, oh well
hit out to the man on the sweeper cover boundary off the back foot
gentle length delivery around off, he stands tall and punches it wide of sweeper cover
wanted to cut this one through point, but it was too full for the shot and he ended up bottom edging it towards Umar Akmal at backward point
played out to mid off
112 kph slower one on the pads, he waits for it to arrive and flicks it, all wrists and no feet, wide of long on
misses out, it was wide and short of a good length outside off, but he punched it straight to Afridi at extra cover
Kamran saves some runs, it was down the leg side, and Guptill helped it on its way, but Kamran dives to his left to pull off the stop
very full outside off, Ryder plays a check drive that beats a diving extra cover and goes wide of sweeper cover
eased down the ground to long on
Guptill misses out again, short and wide, a bit slower, he cuts it straight to backward point
worked away in front of the wicket on the leg side for another single
brings up the 100 stand in good time with a sweep to fine leg off a full toss
too close for the cut, but Guptill plays the shot anyways, and gets it to sweeper cover for a run
length delivery on the stumps, the Razzaq speciality, no room at all, pushed down the track
angled in to the stumps, fuller too, allows him to clip it down to long on
looks to smash this one down the ground, but mistimes it, still enough on it to go over Razzaq on the bounce
marginally shorter, but bang on the stumps, worked away to long on for yet another single
for the first time, a swing and a miss from Jesse, had a swing across the line to a slower one outside off, and was a bit early on the shot
mistimes the glide to third man, and finds that backward point has got to it quickly, Guptill sends him back
some turn for Shahid, but wide outside off and cut away in front of point
flighted delivery, he was eyeing another big swing, but it was very full and he eased it down to long on in the end
Guptill keeps going for the cut shot, this one was too close and quicker too, and he was beaten
driven off the front foot wide of extra cover
had no clue about the wrong 'un, played down the wrong line looking to work it past midwicket, but the ball turned the other way to take the outside edge through the vacant slip region
slow turn for Shahid, guided to point off the front foot
comes forward and pushes a length ball to cover

almost carries to a diving Umar Gul at mid off, Ryder had creamed the full delivery in the air, and it would have been a certain boundary had Umar not gone leaping to his right, he got a hand to it in the end but it had already fallen short
driven back to the bowler who gets a hand to it and prevents the single
the middle stump is knocked back, the non-striker's that is, Guptill smashed this fullish one straight, too straight past the bowler, and found the stumps in the way
goes across the stumps and wristily flicks to midwicket

has him flicking across the line to a length delivery around off stump, the outside edge scoots away to third man, could have gone to backward point, but New Zealand have had their share of luck in this innings
flighted delivery pushed in front of cover
lovely delivery, the one that went across and kicked off the surface, had Jesse reaching for it outside off stump, and beat him totally
opens the bat face at the last instant to one on off stump to guide it to Shoaib at short third man
slammed off the front foot, that man Umar Gul gets in the way again, this time at extra cover
yet another single through extra cover
fuller outside off stump, driven forcefully down the ground to long off
gets forward and hits this length delivery wide of cover
one more swing and a miss from Jesse, he is eyeing cow corner, swung across the line, and it passed perilously close to off stump
Jesse with that effortless and stylish glide off the back foot, but this time straight to point
he was a but lazy here in getting his bat down in time, it was tapped in front of point, and Jesse did not stretch out to get into the crease, direct hit and he was gone
fuller on the stumps, flicked elegantly to midwicket
hammered down the ground, where a diving long off saves three runs, Shoaib it was, good effort from the ageing fast bowler
guided very late to short third man, almost off the keeper's gloves
worked away through square leg
waits an instant before lofting this full one over and wide of extra cover
Guptill backs way to cut another one on off stump, but cannot get it past point
the faster one, steered to a very fine short third man
good tight over from the captain, played back down the track
looks for the swing to fine leg, squirts off the pads behind square on the leg side
goes back in the crease and pushes a short of a length delivery to long on, efficiently done, nothing cute, just accumulating the runs
Jesse is throwing his bat at everything now, backs away way outside leg stump, Razzaq goes wider outside off, he slashes it wide of third man
driven on the bounce to the bowler who gets a hand to it and prevents the single

well ,well, it's not Jesse but Guptill who has thrown away yet another start, it was full and on middle and leg, Guptill in his endeavor to smash it out of the ground, only got as far as long on, who timed his leap nicely to take the catch, Pakistan have broken through, and another NZ batsman has wasted a start
gets the bat in front of pad just in time to defend this angled delivery towards midwicket
cut away wide of sweeper cover
down on one knee and goes for the sweep, it dipped on him and he bottom edged it down to short fine leg
nicely forward and pushes a flat delivery to extra cover
worked away in front of square off the front foot
flicks a full toss straight to midwicket
gets to the pitch of a fuller one and drives it to long off with the full face of the bat, holds the pose for effect, he can afford to do that, he has Baz on his side
looks to force this one through extra cover off the back foot, and gets an inside edge backward of square
back of a length delivery pushed away to mid off

loud shout for lbw, Taylor had planted that front foot down, and was late in getting his bat in front to play the attempted flick, the length delivery crashed in to the pads in front of middle, Razzaq went up in appeal right away, umpire Hill said no even faster, that looked gone, he is fortunate to be out there
arrests the front foot movement to push this one back to the bowler
pinches a single with a push to mid on
swung lazily through square leg, good fielding on the boundary keeps them to a single
this one came back in a touch from around on a length on off, Jesse was pushing at it from the crease, he is struggling with the feet movement, the ball rolled away to mid off
again plays a forcing shot from the crease, Gul brings it back in even more, and he ends up hitting it back to the bowler
brings up the 150 with a carve over point off a wide and full delivery, just went through with the shot without moving the feet much
Taylor gets the chance to play his ferocious cut, but there is a man at sweeper cover, and he keeps them to a couple
opens the face of the bat and runs down this length delivery to third man
141 kph near-yorker from Gul, Ryder goes nowhere with the feet, and somehow manages to keep this delivery out

got 'em! Razzaq has struck again, gets rid of Taylor this time, it was bowled in the channel outside off on a length, Taylor got sucked in to the drive, ended up playing a feeble one in the end, and the faint outside edge settled low in to Kamran's gloves, Razzaq breaks in to a wide grin, Pakistan's fightback in this game continues
eases a length delivery off the front foot to mid off
Franklin decides to let this length delivery go, it pitched marginally outside  leg stump, and he took it high on the pad, there was not much of an appeal from Pakistan, height was an issue as well
worked away through square leg this time, Franklin is away
played out towards mid off
Jesse goes for maximum, and gets it too, it was a rare poor delivery from Razzaq, down the leg side, and he swung it cleanly, high and over the fine leg boundary
swing it like Jesse, but caress it like Franklin, leans out to this one outside off and sends it purring through extra cover, not more than a gentle push
goes for the bouncer, wide and high over the batsman, and is called wide by the umpire
gets some away movement from the batsman from a length outside off, but after it has passed Franklin who was shouldering arms anyways
goes straight on a length close to off, Franklin is forward and pushing it towards extra cover
driven wide of sweeper cover, who swoops down on the ball to quell all thoughts of a second
waits for a full delivery on the crease, and at the very last moment guides it to backward point
has a lazy waft outside off stump to a back of a length delivery, Kamran collects
length delivery in the off stump channel, hit away to sweeper cover off the back foot
Jesse continues to swing, continues to connect, and the ball keeps dropping short of the fielders, this one fell in front of a desperately diving Shehzad at fine leg, and went in to the boundary
played out to backward point off the back foot
takes a step out, and check drives a fullish delivery to sweeper cover
another batsman hits the stumps, now it is Franklin, driven as straight as you can get past the bowler, and hits the middle stump at the other end
Shoaib drops it short and wide, but the pace and extra bounce beats the slash from Franklin
tossed up delivery from round the stumps played out to midwicket
floated up on middle, he reaches out to push it to extra cover
bang on target from Hafeez, played back to the bowler
driven to extra cover off the front foot
worked away through square leg off the back foot, it was angled in on the pads
slow and coming into Jesse, played away back to the bowler
Shoaib beats Franklin who wants to have a go at a length delivery outside off

Franklin repeats the shot that had him beaten off the previous delivery, this time he gets the outside edge through to Kamran who went down to his left to take a good low catch, Shoaib holds his arms aloft
driven off the front foot through cover
moves to 99 with an airy flick past the diving man at midwicket, it was far from him though

Jesse gets to his century with what he has been doing all innings, Shoaib gives him a gift on the pads, and he flicks it to the fine leg boundary, pumps his fists in celebration as the crowd stand to applaud a special knock
Shoaib beats Jesse this time with one that goes across Ryder on a length, who has a poke at it from the crease
driven down to long on
hit down the ground to long on
driven off the front foot to long  on
driven in the air to long on for another run
targets the single to long on again but this time it goes to Afridi at midwicket
comes on the front foot to flick it to long on from wide of off stump, but gets it again to midwicket
gets one on middle and leg and plays it out to midwicket
makes some room outside leg stump, and goes for the forcing shot through the off side, but mistimes it to extra cover
now goes for the pull to a widish delivery outside off stump, ends up flailing in the air, was nowhere near the ball
118 kph slower ball around off, and that late glide from Jesse, twirls it down to third man
Styris gets one short and wide enough for the cut, but gets only the single to sweeper cover
Jesse is swinging wildly now, was again not remotely close to this wide one outside off, but still shaped up for an ungainly pull that found thin air
gets the scoop away wide of fine leg, went down on a knee and took it right off middle stump
gives him the charge down the track, Hafeez bowls it shorter, and Jesse pushes it to extra cover
swings a full one hard down to long on
on the front foot and driven to long on

Ryder has finally holed out, it was in the slot, tossed up on leg stump, and he went for the lofted shot over wide long on, but did not get enough meat on the shot, ended up hitting it straight to deep midwicket, he has played his part in this innings though
played out in front of the wicket off the front foot
back of a length outside off, punched to point off the back foot
much fuller, still outside off, hit out to backward point
goes on the back foot and runs down a length delivery to third man
brutal from Scott, cuts a length delivery hard, and gets it wide of third man, it wasn't that far from him, but was struck very firmly, the man had no chance
more power from Styris, this time he gets it wide of sweeper cover off the back foot
super delivery from Gul, pitches around off and straightens to go past the defensive blade of Nathan who was pinned on the back foot
takes this one that turns into him from off, and works it through midwicket
played out to midwicket off the back foot
tossed up on the stumps, Nathan gets it down to long on with the drive
eases this one down the ground for another single
shortish and turning in, cut away in front of sweeper cover for a couple, and the 200 is up
a touch short for the drive, he goes for it, and ends up hitting it in the air, but it falls well short of Hafeez
a touch short from Shahid, whipped away off the back foot through midwicket
punched to extra cover off the back foot
has a go at this fuller one outside off, and the outside edge falls short of short third man
hit away to extra cover who saves the single with a diving stop
the wrong 'un, he was looking to force it off the back foot, and hit it in to the ground off the inner half of the bat
flat and quick, played out to extra cover, good over
flicked away down the ground off the front foot
driven down to long on
the man at long on continues to be kept busy with another one driven to him
pushes forward and drives to extra cover
another one punched stylishly down to long on off the back foot
driven in the air again back to the bowler, but Styris is in the way of Hafeez as he attempts to catch the ball, but fails, it drops a touch short too
played out to extra cover off the front foot
slashes at a quick and full one outside off, and gets a thick edge that hurries fine down the off side for a boundary
loopy slow delivery goes down the leg side
fuller and around off, hit along the ground to long off
flat and fast from Shahid, he gets forward to defend to extra cover

simple run out chance missed, it was played out behind point, and Styris rushed for a single, was more than halfway down before being sent back, Afridi messed up the collection, and the ball rolled away off his hands, he kicks the ground in frustration
played out to point
whipped away in front of square leg
tossed up delivery, pushed back to the bowler, the spinners have done a fine job
saves another single with a dive to his right to field the drive
in his quest to go wide of the bowler, he finds Afridi at midwicket
flat on the stumps, punched away to Afridi at midwicket again
gets the single on the fifth attempt, with a push off a full delivery to long on
goes down the leg side, and he helps himself to four runs with a flick that sends it wide of fine leg
raps him on the pads with a skiddy one that beats his waft across the line, but was sliding down leg with that angle
cannot get away the slippery short of a length delivery past midwicket
makes room to tap it in front of point, and the single is on
goes way down the leg side with that angle from round the stumps, he has been all over the place today, and for most of the series
101 kph slower ball, Styris had lined up for the cut, but the ball took ages to arrive and when it did he was not in a position to do anything but have a waft at it
played off the front foot towards mid off
turning in from middle, punched away to midwicket off the back foot
works away a leg stump full toss to deep midwicket
mistimes a cut in to the ground and in front of point for a single
flicks a full toss past midwicket, and Styris scampers back for the second
Nathan gets one in the slot, and lifts it over wide long on, got a tossed up delivery, cleared the front foot, and sent it soaring down the ground
clipped off his toes through midwicket for another single
top edge that lands in no man's land, it was short and fired in, he went for a belated pull, and it swirled in the air, but there was no one near the non-striker's end to take it
full and carved through extra cover, got to the pitch of this one, and picked the gap beautifully
gets beaten outside off stump as this one angles in to him from outside off stump, and he tries to run it down to third man
gets another one to nip back in from outside off stump, he stays in the crease to steer it down to third man
flicked away with the angle wide of midwicket for a single
101 kph slower ball from Tanvir wide outside off stump, Styris is beaten as he goes for the cut without moving his feet
backs away outside leg to have a huge swing, Gul follows him with a full delivery, a single is taken off the inside edge as the ball rolls away in to the on side
now Styris makes rooms outside leg, this time Gul goes full and wide outside off, he squeezes it out to cover
lucky for Styris, went hard at a full delivery around leg stump, got an inside edge that beat short fine leg for a welcome boundary
Gul keeps it full, outside off stump, Styris squeezes it out to extra cover
marginally short, and he quickly goes on the back foot to pull it to deep square leg
clobbered! he pitched it short, and it sat up on Nathan, who took a step back, and thumped it flat and straight over the bowler's head, he hit it so well it went all the way
wrong 'un, worked away through square leg
lifted over mid off, Nathan just remains in the crease, backs away to leg stump, and thwacks a short ball over the infield
bowls it fuller, makes no difference, Nathan has creamed this one in the gap at extra cover off the front foot
hit out to midwicket off the back foot
hit down the ground wide of long off
this is good batting, it was worked in to the gap between deep midwicket and long on, and they came back for the second, quite comfortably in the end, 13 off the over
slower one gone wrong down the leg side, helped away backward of square leg off the hips, and that runs into the boundary
crack! another slower one despatched into oblivion, it wasn't short enough but sat up to be disdainfully pulled over deep midwicket
another shortish one, he looks to carve him through the off side, but mishits it straight past the non-striker's stumps
he goes fuller this time, but his nightmare continues, Nathan had a go at it,and got a thick outside edge down to the third man boundary
take that! this is poor bowling, really is, full and wide outside off stump, Nathan goes down on a knee and lofts it over extra cover for another boundary, 19 taken so far with one ball to go
anti-climax, ends up hitting this length delivery back to the bowler
lofts one down the ground, but not cleanly enough, gets only a single down to long off
looks for the big flick over midwicket, but Gul follows him down the leg side with a full one, and it bounds off the pads to short third man
Styris brings up his 50, working a length delivery past midwicket for a couple
full and in the blockhole on middle, cannot get it tighter than that, Styris backs away outside leg and squeezes it to extra cover
dropped full and outside off, he heaves it wide of Shoaib at long off, who is very slow to get to his left and lets the ball go through his hands, and in to the boundary

gets a high full toss, and swings it straight down the throat of deep square leg, but hello, it is called a no-ball for height, it was a very marginal call, the ball was just about waist high when it reached the batsman, but he survives
and the extra delivery has cost another boundary, Nathan is swinging wildly at everything, and gets this full delivery high over a leaping short third man
and the 300 is up for NZ as Styris waits on a shortish ball on the leg stump, and helps it to fine leg for a boundary
heaved in to the leg side for a single
cramps him up for room on leg stump, but he still slogs it wide of deep midwicket for a couple
Nathan continues to bosh them down the ground, gets a tossed up one on off stump, and murders it over wide long off for maximum
he is gone now! died swinging in the end, another full one was lofted down the ground, but he got too much underneath the pitch of this one, and long on took the straightforward catch

Mills is run out without facing a ball, it was driven down to long on, Shehzad covered good ground to his right, Mills wanted the second, Styris didn't, in the end Mills turned half-heartedly back, but even though he put in the dive, the throw was pinpoint accurate, and Kamran whipped off the bails, Mills trudges off shaking his head, but the headache is now Pakistan's, as they face a mountain of a target to chase

inn2.comm: off the mark right away, pushing a short of a good length delivery on middle and leg to mid on, and they go through for the single

dropped Mills produces the edge with the perfect outswinger, pitched around of and moved away just enough to produce an edge off the attempted drive, the ball flew in between slip and Baz, who went diving to his right with one hand, and clanged it
played out to extra cover off the back foot
straight in the channel outside off stump, left alone
goes for the magic outswinger again, but fails to conjure it up, he goes back to defend the back of a length delivery down the track
good start from Mills, bowls another one in the corridor outside off which is left alone
fuller length on the stumps, driven wristily to mid on
takes a step outside off stump even before the bowler enters his delivery stride, Southee ends up spraying it wide outside of stump, got some away shape on that one
he is away with a swat through midwicket, it wasn't short enough but he got enough bat on it to muscle it away for the first boundary of the innings
he goes full down the pads, and Shehzad flicks it away just short of a diving short fine leg
one hand comes off the bat handle as he stretches forward to drive this full and wide delivery to cover
fullish on the pads, and Hafeez picks it cleanly over square leg for another boundary
gets forward to drive this overpitched one wide of extra cover
driven off the front foot in to the thickly populated off side cordon
nice away shape from Mills, brings it in from back of a length and takes it away, he has a flail at it from the crease, and is beaten
played out to mid on off the back foot
another full pitched away moving delivery, driven to extra cover off the front foot

Shehzad departs to a brain fade, he decided to give Mills the charge, Mills dropped it short, and he went for a pull-swat, was in no position for the shot, the top-edge settled in to the hands of How behind point
gets a back of a length ball and plays it out to a shortish point
with fine leg in the circle, Southee goes down the pads, and is picked away easily to the right to that man
Guptill saves runs, goes flying to his right at extra cover, Southee has gone wide and full outside off this time and was thumped off the front foot
off a thick outside edge to third man as he pushes at this back of a length delivery from the crease
pushed out to point off the back foot
keeps down a back of a length ball with soft hands and takes a quick run as it rolls away to mid on
Hafeez goes over square leg, and goes all the way, Southee continues to stray down the leg side, and Hafeez just whipped it over deep square leg with a flick of the wrists
punches this short of a length ball down to mid off
misses out on the attempted flick and takes a length ball on the pads
Mills has settled in to the short of a good length stuff, Kamran stands tall and punches it to mid off
marginally fuller and he reaches out to drive it in front of point
in the channel outside off stump, left alone, good carry through to the keeper

gets on the front foot to drive this length ball wide of mid off and they take the single, think about an overthrow as the ball goes in to the leg side, but abandon such dangerous thoughts as the backing up is good
and goes down the leg side right away with a length delivery
comes forward to push a length ball towards mid off, they take a couple of steps towards each other, and then get back to safety
full length delivery, again on the leg stump, whipped through midwicket, but there is a man in the deep now
goes for the pull to a pacy short delivery that skids on, and is beaten even as he goes hard at the ball

well, well, would you believe it, another full delivery on the pads, and it gets a wicket, Hafeez flicks it wristily, but picks out Franklin at deep square leg who does not have to move much to take that one
ripper from Bennett! too good even for someone of Younis' class, pitches around off and straightens, rushing past his defensive prod
thuds high on to thigh pad from back of a length as Younis wafts weakly across the line
comes forward, covers for the away shape from a length outside off, and drives it wide of mid off for a single
punches a short of a length ball to short cover off the back foot
gets across and pushes a length delivery down to mid on
arrests the across movement as Mills angles one into him from a length, and defends it back to the bowler
nearly chopped it on to the stumps, it was short of a good length, but not wide enough to be forced through point, which Younis tried, and got an inside edget that somehow did not land on the stumps
pushes this one off the back foot in front of cover to get off the mark
taps a length delivery towards extra cover, and sets off for the single, before being rightly sent back by Kamran
does not get hold of the pull off a short delivery, but still gets it through midwicket for a couple of rus
tucked away off the hips backward of square leg for another couple
not short enough for the pull, but he does so nevertheless, and gets it along the ground in front of square leg for a single
mid on is deep, Kamran knows that as he pushes one in that direction and goes through for a well-judged single
fuller this time, driven off the front foot wide of extra cover
comes forward, opens the bat face and guides a length delivery to point, and then sends back Kamran who had come half way down the track searching for a single
pushed away to cover off the back foot
Mills goes down the leg side now, and Younis clips him away to the right of short fine leg for a boundary
tapped to covers for a run
and again, comes forward, plays the ball softly towards cover and the single is on
has a go at a wide delivery outside off stump, the foot was not to the pitch of the ball, and he was beaten on the drive
played out in the direction of point off the back foot
tries to pull a not-short-enough delivery, doesn't time it at all, Bennett has overstepped meanwhile
123 kph slower ball from the back of the hand, Kamran goes for the pull again, is early in to the shot, and ends up swinging ungainly in the air
driven solidly to the left of mid on who runs across and fields
full and wide outside off, driven on the bounce to Scott at short extra cover
100 kph loopy slower one, dies down on Kamran outside off stump as he comes forward to drive, checks his shot in the end to push it towards extra cover
106 kph slower ball, but this one goes wrong, way down the leg side, but Kamran manages to get a faint tickle on it as he tries to help it fine, and Bennett gets away
stretches out and opens the face of the bat to steer a very wide delivery down to third man
Kamran has a heave-ho and connects neatly, it was bowled on a length and angling into Kamran, who swung it over mid on for a one-bounce boundary
gets behind the line to defend this one outside off towards extra cover
straight driven all along the ground, but long on is in place now
short and wide for the cut, but it is the slower one, and though Younis wait s on it an instant, he cannot beat point
bottom edges the cut in to the ground and they take on the throw from point, safely in the end for a run
is in some discomfort as he misses an attempted pull off a shortish one and is hit on the box, ouch! takes some time to catch his breath, and the guard has actually cracked, he holds it up sheepishly
nicely rides the bounce on a short of a good length ball that gets big on him outside off, and keeps it down in front of point for a single
105 kph slower ball, pushed away towards extra cover for another run
one more slower ball on the pads, he adjusts late to flick it to short fine leg
cuts a shortish one wide of point and they go through for another single

Baz has made up for his drop earlier, and pulled off a stunner, it was a thick outside edge that was travelling far to his right, he went flying in the air and pouched it with both hands, it was a fullish delivery and Younis went for the drive with an open bat face from the crease, Pakistan in trouble now
goes for the cut but cannot beat point
punched off the back foot to extra cover
brings down the bat to squeeze a length delivery backward of point for a single
caught in the crease as he tries to defend this delivery angled in to him, off the inside edge on to pad
defended hurriedly to mid on as this one skids on to him
pushed out in front of point off the back foot, Shafiq is slow in responding to the call, but makes it to the non-striker's end safely
defended to cover off the front foot, Bennet is bowling at lively pace, and thudding it in to the bat
a touch short, he goes back and pulls it away through square leg
132 kph but he is certainly hurrying it through, skidded after pitching back of a length around off, and Kamran had a poke at it from the crease
slower one goes off target and down the leg side
pins him on the back foot with a back of a length delivery that has him hopping to defend it in to the off side

almost got him, it was slashed hard, and rocketed high and to the right of Brendon who almost pulled off another spectacular take, diving high to his right, but the ball had taken a healthy edge and was was too quick for him
driven off the front foot down to long on
tries the tap-to-cover-and-run, shafiq had taken off almost half way down the pitch before being sent back, had to dive in the end to make his ground
driven to sweeper cover for a single
skids on to him from a length outside off, he is stuck on the crease and gets an inside edge on to pad
another inside edge on to pad, he is slow to defend these skiddy deliveries that are rushing on to him from a length
gets one on the pads and happily flicks it away to fine leg
gets a back of a length delivery around off, and pushes it in front of cover off the back foot for a single
shortish and wide outside off, cut away to sweeper cover
nicely forward in defence to a flat one on middle
mistimes a cut in to the ground to a diving short extra cover
played out towards cover
goes for the cut, and it goes in the air wide of a diving backward point, valiant attempt but it was too far from him
goes down on a knee for the fine sweep from middle, Brendon saw him doing that and went down the leg side, but he beat him with the shot and got enough on it to go all the way
tossed up full outside off, driven to sweeper cover
guided behind point with an open face off the front foot
comes forward and pushes back to the bowler
stretches forward and guides this fullish ball in front of point
pushed away through point off the back foot
works a flat one to midwicket and wants the single, but the throw comes in quickly and he has to retreat back
tossed up a touch, and eased back to the bowler
forced down the ground off the front foot to long off
has him reaching out outside off stump, and he plays it out to short extra cover
goes across and forward, and works this one in front of midwicket
Kamran gives Woodcock the charge, gets to the pitch of this flighted one, and swings it high over mid on for six
pushed out to extra cover who dives to this right and saves the single
looks to steer a fullish delivery outside off, and is beaten
played out to midwicket, still no run
short and turning in, he goes back and cut it away to sweeper cover
96 kph delivery, it hurries on to him, and he squeezes it out to point
another faster one, this time he got a bit more width, and cut it away behind point, and wide of the man at sweeper cover for a useful boundary
driven to extra cover off the front foot, Kamran is cross with himself as he hit it to the fielder
whipped away through midwicket
takes this one from off stump, and cuts it away to sweeper over
flat on off stump, he pushes it past Guptill as extra cover, and as soon as the ball passes him, they take the single
works this one through midwicket
Kamran is taking Woodcock for some runs here, waltzes down the track, is right to the pitch again, and swings it straight down the ground for another maximum
off the inside edge through square leg as he pushes from the back foot
pushed down the ground to long on
long on is a busy man again as another fuller one is driven down to him
turning in from outside off, but way too short, he rocks back to cut it wide of sweeper cover
stylishly pushed out to midwicket
driven hard down the ground, Nathan gets a hand to it, but the ball bounds off towards long on
one more single is added to the total through a gentle push down the ground
gentle length delivery, safely pushed to point and a harmless single results
backs away to late cut a length ball from off stump, but right to short third man
back of a length, punched solidly to long on off the back foot
Asad comes down the track, Styris shortens the length and he plays it out to midwicket
goes down the leg side, Asad misses the flick, Baz misses the take, and the ball loops away fine down the leg side
stands in the crease and brings up his half century with a confident push in the region of long on
the best area to target for all those singles, down the ground, this time to long on
flicked away to short fine leg who gathers the ball quickly to prevent the run
another single down to long on with a drive along the ground
drives against the turn to long off this time
very delicate late cut, waited to it to turn in from outside off and used the pace to glide it past short third man who chased it all the way to the boundary
pings long on with a drive to get a run
loud appeal for lbw it caught him on the crease, came in after pitching on a length, it looked very close, height did not seem an issue, replays show that it would have hit the top of middle
comes forward and drive down the ground
takes it from middle stump as he goes down on a knee and sweeps him fine for a boundary
pushed to long off for a single

and Pakistan have gifted away a wicket! the old tap-and-run to cover, except they seemed to be engulfed by doubt and confusion about the running part, Shafiq had to turn back in the end, but the throw was accurate enough to beat him to the crease, and Brendon did the rest
is off the mark with a push off the back foot to cover
starts from around the wicket and finds a decent length, it's nudged around the corner. Tidy start
pushed firmly to mid-off and the call was "yes, yes, one, one, one". You'd think these two would know how to run with each other
Franklin delivers a slower ball, there aren't many quick ones in his armoury, and an inside edge makes its way past a diving mid-off
inexplicably Umar plays and misses outside off stump. Perhaps it kept a touch low
carefully driven, without much timing back towards the bowler
and again Umar is beaten outside off stump. Just pushing without much footwork. Sort of thing that ruined him in the Test series in England
Styris continues his exhibition of filthy medium pace, he is very accurate though and the best Kamran can manage is to push down the ground
steered backwards of point for another scampered single
slower ball, offcutter of sorts, but that makes it seem more vicious than it was. A cut shot was mistimed backwards of square for a swift single
and again pushed a few metres wide of point for a single
ah, this is true tumble-weed-rolling middle-over milking, steered to short third man for a single
leg bye completes the single-a-ball over, thudding off the pads into space. Good work from Team Akmal there
not so much a call as a growl as Umar steered this to point and thought about a single which wasn't there
Franklin overpitched a touch and Umar cracked a straight drive, the bowler tried to guide it onto the stumps at the non-strikers end but missed the target and mid-on cleaned up
driven this time firmly wide of extra cover
firmly clunked down the ground for a gentle single
Franklin finds a good length and line hugging off stump and all Umar can do is block

Franklin creates an angle by aiming towards middle, Umar's response is to shuffle across his stumps and guide a single to midwicket. Almost like Jonathan Trott, though with more style and less effectiveness
"these dots are great lads" is the call from the New Zealand keeper. I suppose they are
Styris misdirects another slower ball, just heading down the leg side, but crucially for him it flicks a pad and bobbles away
this time Umar gets the single, working around the corner
this is classic Kiwi-dobber good work. Straight, no pace on the ball and the drive is fielded smartly by the bowler
Kamran, like the rest of us, has had enough. He gets a slower-ball, clears his front leg and thumps it over long-on for six! 150 up, and in good style
flicked around the corner this time
full and wide, there for the drive, he gets to the pitch and creams it along the ground wide of sweeper cover for a couple
this time he goes shorter, and in to the body, Kamran goes back and drops it close to the wicket on the off side
Franklin gets it a touch straight on middle, and is picked away in front of midwicket for a single
goes a lot fuller, but same result, tucked away  neatly through midwicket for one more
the length is alright, but the angle from round the stumps allows Kamran to work it away in front of mid on

Franklin strikes! it was dug in shorter this time, bounced and straightened around off stump, squeezed out the edge from Umar as he looked to steal a single to third man with the open face, how long can Kamran sustain Pakistan's chase with  all the trauma at the other end?
Styris continues with his gentle length deliveries, and one of those is driven back down the track
Kamran continues with his accumulation, guides one to third man to pinch another single, brings Afridi on strike
he wants to pounce on his first delivery like a man in a hurry, but midwicket slows down his pull shot, in fact, he stops it
strikes him on the pads, but that was sliding down leg, and Afridi gets away with swinging merrily across the line
steered to short third man, Afridi thinks there is a single to be stolen, Kamran wants to have none of the spoils, and sends his captain back, just in time too
Styris goes fuller, and at his pace, is easily taken for a single to long on

lovely timing from Kamran, boy, this is so good to watch, it was cut without any hint of violence, but the ball sped away with brilliant timing, and beat third man who wasn't that far away from it to begin with
this time he pulls a shortish Franklin delivery through midwicket
Afridi continues to live on he edge, but survives, looked to steer a length delivery to third man, but it straightened past his angled bat
when he connects cleanly, the only doubt is whether it will go beyond the ropes or not. this one is murdered over mid on for a boundary
drives to sweeper cover and gets the single
silky drive from Kamran for a run down to long off
goes full but on the pads, and Kamran expertly avoids the man at midwicket with the forceful drive
still more leg sidish stuff from Southee, but this time the length is a touch shorter and Kamran finds the man at midwicket
no problems with this one, gets behind it and sends it down to long on for the umpteenth time in the day
Afridi forces the length delivery through extra cover, there is so much bottom hand on that and that's why he cannot get any worthwhile timing on ot
bowls one on a length, but Kamran pushes it in to the off side and scampers through for the run
Afridi gets one he cannot muscle away through the on side, it was a bit fuller on leg stump, and he plays it out to midwicket quietly
Kamran tries the old hoick over cow corner, but does not connect cleanly, the ball flies in the air wide of mid on but the rolls away limply to be fielded for the cost of a couple

Franklin has the big one! Kamran has hit him right to short extra cover, it is Taylor who generally lurks in those areas, and Kamran drove the full pitched delivery in to his hands, Kamran is despondent, he gets an ovation as he departs
gets one too wide outside off to interest him in to any action
he is off the mark with a push in front of cover off the back foot
whips wristily from outside off stump, but a single to midwicket is all he gets

Afridi almost fell off the edge he has been living on in this innings, Razzaq had played it out to Guptill at cover, and Afridi wanted the single, before realising haflway down the pitch that it was probably not a very good idea, he was so far out he even gave up the attempt to make it back, but the throw missed, and Afridi lives on till the next adventure

another one gone! the slip has brought New Zealand a wicket, Franklin lured Razzaq in to a fatal drive, and Taylor rarely drops dollies at slip, he rarely drops dollies anywhere, and gobbles the ball up in his hands
pushed out to point and Afridi goes in search of another single, the throw comes in, there's no one backing up close, and they take the gift, that brings Tanvir on strike
almost got the edge, Tanvir went for an elegant drive, but the ball zipped away off the seam from round the wicket, Baz knows how close it was, and grimaces, in a happy sort of way
thuds in to the forward defensive push from Tanvir
now he angles this one across the left-hander from over the stumps, and he hangs out his bat in defiant defence
Tanvir is off the mark helping himself to four with a neat tickle off his pads as Southee errs in line
bowls it fuller now, Tanvir is up to it, and blocks it solidly in to the covers
a solid defensive push from Afridi towards point, three steps down the pitch, and back in to the crease
Mills takes it away from a length around off stump, and also past Afridi's tentative poke
gets him to drive, Afridi gets away with a thick edge down to third man
Tanvir dead bats the delivery going across him
now he tickles this one leaving him to third man to bring Afridi back on strike
comfortably pushed wide of midwicket for a still more comfortable single
looks to thump it  through the off side, but then drives this length delivery along the ground to extra cover
wide open spaces in front of covers beckoning tantalisingly for a single to be taken, and Afridi onliges, a push to the off side and he gets to the other end
targets Tanvir with the yorker, doesn;t get it exactly in the slot, and Tanvir digs it out hurriedly
now he bowls one to Sohail on the pads, and he picks him through square leg
Afridi slaps this length delivery to sweeper cover and trots down the pitch
a gentle glide to third man for a calm single
another steer down to third man, and Sohail gets down to the other end
turns one on a length on middle stump to mid on and crosses over for one
Tanvir abandons the steer, the glide and all those niceties, and goes hard at one wide outside off stump, Baz has no chance with the thick edge
firm push to cover off the back foot and an emphatic decision not to go for the suicidal single
works this one wide of long on and wider of deep midwicket and by the time those two gentlemen arrive near the ball, Sohail has run two
wants to send this one going across him through extra cover. but the feet don't get moving much, and the ball continues on its path to the keeper
Afridi is content to work the singles at the moment, still no Powerplay, none more run to extra cover
if it weren't for the mounting asking rate, this would be pretty efficient middle overs batting, a tap in front of cover and they take the single

Afridi takes cognizance of the runrate and tries to sweep this one to fine leg, but is hit on the glove, then on the pad, Franklin goes up in loud appeal, don't know for what, even the umpire does not know why
Tanvir steals a single wide of midwicket with an honest push
109 kph slower one, Afridi bashes it to extra cover, goes 'yeah. yeah' and completes the single, that the throw does not hit the stumps definitely helps
Tanvir goes down the ground, over mid off and in to the boundary on the bounce, just took a step forward and swung the fullish delivery cleanly
Bennett bowls a slower one, Afridi throws his might at it, and sends it racing to sweeper cover despite one hand coming off the bat handle
hits a length on the stumps, and Tanvir blocks it neatly
pings one off Sohail's helmet, hits him flush on the side of the headgear, Tanvir went right in the path of the bouncer taking his eyes off the ball
lovely bowling, the bouncer pegs Tanvir back, and he has a poke from the crease at one going across him
he is getting edgy for the single, cannot get one, point comes in the way of his back foot push
has an earnest swipe at this length delivery and sends it scooting down to long on to retain the strike

Tanvir is playing a useful little knock here, lifts Franklin's friendly length delivery over midwicket for a boundary, he stands still and then suddenly breaks free at the last moment in a burst of arms
misses out  on the flick, takes it on the pads, Franklin is interested but that would have gone down leg
Afridi is giving Tanvir the strike here, flicks one backward of square leg
Afridi is off the blocks even as Tanvir blocks one to Taylor at extra cover, but has to dive back in but Ross surprisingly decided not to have a go
gives him the slower one outside off stump, and Tanvir is beaten as he looks to hustle it through point
jeez, how effective is that, Tanvir waits for this short of a length ball to arrive and then plays it very late to the left of a diving Brendon for another boundary
boom boom explodes, gets one with some room to break free, gets under it and upper cuts it for maximum wide of third man
another one, the slow bouncer gone wrong, Afridi was waiting for it for ages to arrive, and when it did, he swatted it wide of deep midwicket for four
he lands one on a length outside off stump, Afridi thinks there is enough room to cut, but there wasn;t in fact, and Brendon collects the ball
118 kph slower one on target this time, full and outside off, Afridi does not know how to milk it for runs, tries the dab to third man, but the ball limply rolls way to Baz
murders another fuller and slower one but straight to sweeper cover
teasing one full and wide outside off, Tanvir has a go and misses, don't know whose good fortune it is
turns this full toss down to fine leg, wants a second, the throw is off target too, but Tanvir does not want to take the risk
right in the blockhole, Tanvir cannot do much about those, is beaten as he tries to squeeze it to point, Afridi frets at the other end
another low full pitched delivery outside off stump, he cannot get the bat down in time and another precious dot ball results
almost makes it three in three, but Tanvir stretches it out to extra cover and they take a single
Shahid gets the boundary for the over, Southee helps him with a nice easy full toss on the leg stump, and Afridi thwacks it backward of square leg, one foot in the air as he plays the shot

has Southee pulled off a stunner? He has, Afridi got one in the blockhole and dug it out close to the stumps, Tanvir was pretty slow to get going, and what's more he did not slide his bat in, in fact it got stuck inches short of the crease, and Southee removed the bails with a horizontal leap, super stuff from the quick man, Pakistan sink further
Bennett continues to get his slower ones on target, it bounces gently over Afridi as he misses out the heave
this one has gone wrong too, Afridi was ready for it, saw it early and hammered it over extra cover for a boundary

take that! Afridi brings up 250 with a loft over long on's head, just cleared the front leg, backed away outside leg, and even though Bennett followed him, the momentum deposited the ball into stratosphere
135 kph bouncer, Afridi had again made room outside leg stump, and was surprised with the short one as it sailed past him

Nathan has held on to a scorcher here, how has he survived this one? Afridi had mowed it brutally down the ground, Nathan was in the way at deepish mid off, and put his body behind the line of the ball, and went down with the booty, he now has a toothy grin, but he wouldn't want to be in the way of these missiles often, Pakistan;s chances end with Afridi's departure
stays on the crease to a full pitched ball and thick-edges it down to squarish third man
pacy full delivery but down the leg side, he gets into a tangle as he tries to flick it fine
Shoaib goes miles outside leg stump, and then looks to swipe at a full delivery that somehow contrives to miss leg stump
thumped down to mid on, Southee is keeping them full and up to the stumps
spirited down the ground for a single
throws his might at it, but does not make contact as the ball again misses the stumps
now he backs away and has a go once more, but this is the slower one, of course it misses the wickets as well

Jamie shows How it is done, Gul went for the hoick over midwicket, got it off the toe end of the bat, and the ball went miles in the air, against the backdrop of the evening sky at Auckland, but it had to come down, and How took a well-judged catch, and New Zealand have another win, only their second in 16 games
